          <div class="blog-detail-text-box">
            <p>
              An effective due diligence exercise involves several key steps. It
              begins with a comprehensive search at the relevant Land Registry
              to confirm the registered owner and check for encumbrances such as
              mortgages or liens. This is followed by a physical inspection to
              verify boundaries against survey plans and to check for any
              adverse occupants or competing claims. Additionally, inquiries at
              state and local government planning offices are necessary to
              ensure compliance with zoning regulations. At O. A. Omonuwa SAN &
              Co., we undertake this exhaustive process on behalf of our
              clients, providing them with the clarity and security needed to
              proceed with confidence in their real estate transactions.
            </p>
